snippet.textDisplay: This is not a Punjabi song. This is Seraiki traditional song "CHAN KITHAN GUZARI HAYEE RAAT WE". I have mentioned before that they have changed the words of this traditional song as well, perhaps they can never get the meaning. They say "Menda Ji Daleelan de vaas ve". Which is wrong. Originally it is "Meda Ji daleelan de waat ve". waat is not a Punjabi word, it is a Seraiki word that means "mouth". The sentence means "my soul remained captivated in the mouth of worries". DALEEL here does not mean logic, it means worries in Seraiki. And word IS NOT "Menda"; it is "Meda" and is uttered in Punjabi very differently than uttered in Seraiki. They simply have changed the word they can not speak. It has killed the whole soul and melody of the song.

snippet.textDisplay: The worst havoc one can play with classics is evident from this attempt. For God sake, you guys are mixing three languages in one song: Urdu, Punjabi, and Seraiki. "Chan Kithan" is originally a Seraiki song, sung famously, not originally, by Ata Ullah Khan Esa Kailvi of Mianwali, Pakistan. None of the singers knows the meticulous nuances that differentiate Seraiki from Punjabi and other regional languages including Hindko and Sindhi. It is public rape with the language. For God sake, if you are dying to sing Seraiki songs, please first learn Seraiki, and then sing.

snippet.textDisplay:
THUMBS DOWN from me... many may ask why:
1. The description says Punjabi love-poem, which indeed it is, but they killed the soul of song by changing lyrics to HINDI at many places.
2. Sukhwinder WAS a great singer but now one can easily hear the strains in his voice at higher pitches. It crackles...
3. Such soul songs require best of chorus and they should have been given more emphasis & not the drum beater.
4. In fact all COKE STUDIO songs now start out beautifully and then somewhere too much guitars and drums jump in. :(
5. The only time that Hitesh could get a SUFI song correct was when he invited Nooran sisters.
However a great effort by all other except Sukhwinder Singh (I miss the times of your Chayya Chayya & Munda Southhall daa)
